1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,490
Between now and tomorrow at this time, another 11,500 new consumers will have made their grand entry into the USA.

2
00:00:10,080 --> 00:00:13,010
Population is growing at a record rate.

3
00:00:13,120 --> 00:00:19,410
In the next 10 years, the increase is conservatively estimated at 35 million.

4
00:00:19,760 --> 00:00:25,410
That's equal to the present combined metropolitan population of our five biggest cities,

5
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:29,809
New York, Chicago, Los Angeles, Detroit, and Philadelphia.

6
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:30,849
Imagine.

7
00:00:31,440 --> 00:00:37,890
New industries, new scientific breakthroughs, expanding markets, all spell opportunity.

8
00:00:38,160 --> 00:00:39,490
This is good news.

9
00:00:39,760 --> 00:00:42,849
This is a most wonderful time to be alive.

10
00:00:43,440 --> 00:00:48,450
All signs point to a record demand for top-level people in every field.

11
00:00:48,640 --> 00:00:56,289
people who have superior ability to influence others, to direct their work, to serve them in a leadership capacity.

12
00:00:56,480 --> 00:01:02,849
And the people who will fill these leadership positions are all adults or near-adults right now.

13
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:05,010
One of them is you.

14
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:10,930
The guarantee of a boom is not, of course, a guarantee of personal success.

15
00:01:11,120 --> 00:01:15,569
Over the long pull, the United States has always been booming.

16
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:20,529
But just a fast glance shows that millions and millions of people—in fact,

17
00:01:20,640 --> 00:01:24,450
a majority of them—struggle, but don't really succeed.

18
00:01:24,880 --> 00:01:32,210
The majority of folks still plug along in mediocrity, despite the record opportunity of the last two decades.

19
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:38,289
And in the boom period ahead, most people will continue to worry, to be afraid,

20
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:45,010
to crawl through life feeling unimportant, unappreciated, not able to do what they want to do.

21
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:50,930
As a result, their performance will earn them petty rewards, petty happiness.

22
00:01:51,440 --> 00:01:58,529
Those who convert opportunity into reward, and let me say, I sincerely believe you are one of those,

23
00:01:58,560 --> 00:02:07,329
else you'd rely on luck and not bother with this book, will be those wise people who learn how to think themselves to success.

24
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:08,769
Walk in.

25
00:02:08,880 --> 00:02:12,690
The door to success is open wider than ever before.

26
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:20,049
Put yourself on record now that you are going to join that select group that is getting what it wants from life.

